(In Between)

2
00:01:44,680 --> 00:01:47,599
(Episode 9)

3
00:01:58,680 --> 00:01:59,680
Hello.

4
00:01:59,799 --> 00:02:00,855
Miss, who are you looking for?

5
00:02:00,879 --> 00:02:01,958
I'm looking for Zhou Bin.

6
00:02:01,959 --> 00:02:02,959
Do you have an appointment?

7
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,718
(Senior Partner)

8
00:02:04,719 --> 00:02:07,040
Miss, you can't go in without an appointment.

9
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,120
Miss, you can't go in without an appointment.

10
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,479
Miss.

11
00:02:14,439 --> 00:02:15,529
I'm sorry, Mr. Zhou.

12
00:02:15,530 --> 00:02:16,758
I couldn't stop her.

13
00:02:16,759 --> 00:02:18,479
She said she needs to have a word with you.

14
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:21,920
I do have an appointment with Ms. Sun.

15
00:02:22,199 --> 00:02:23,280
I forgot to tell you.

16
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,816
It's fine. You may leave us alone.

17
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,840
Yes, Mr. Zhou.

18
00:02:32,530 --> 00:02:33,560
Tell me.

19
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:34,720
Where were you last night?

20
00:02:35,840 --> 00:02:36,919
Didn't I send you a photo?

21
00:02:38,319 --> 00:02:40,135
It's a victory party for the client's successful lawsuit.

22
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,199
She was there too.

23
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:44,360
You two were inseparable, holding hands, all lovey-dovey...

24
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:46,479
and she even posted it on her Moments.

25
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,919
What's that supposed to mean?

26
00:02:48,400 --> 00:02:49,960
I'm openly dating you,

27
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,960
yet we have to keep it a secret from everyone.

28
00:02:52,199 --> 00:02:53,319
This is ridiculous.

29
00:02:53,719 --> 00:02:55,639
Why do I feel like I'm some sort of homewrecker?

30
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,960
You care about her...

31
00:02:56,961 --> 00:02:58,559
and you have family ties and business connections.

32
00:02:58,560 --> 00:02:59,639
I can't argue with that.

33
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,879
But could you make sure she's fully settled...

34
00:03:01,919 --> 00:03:02,960
before coming to me?

35
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,999
Why do you keep me hanging like this?

36
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,080
Are you done?

37
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,039
It's my turn now.

38
00:03:10,599 --> 00:03:11,680
I only have one request.

39
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,319
When I'm talking, please don't interrupt me.

40
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,800
Here.

41
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,919
The client yesterday was Zhu Yun Jie.

42
00:03:24,319 --> 00:03:25,879
He's good friends with Zeng Cheng.

43
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,359
It was Zeng Cheng who introduced him to me...

44
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,439
as my client.

45
00:03:28,639 --> 00:03:29,719
It was also him...

46
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,919
who invited Zeng Cheng yesterday.

47
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,919
Let's take a step back.

48
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:37,039
In this kind of situation,

49
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:39,159
I must be in the same frame as her.

50
00:03:42,879 --> 00:03:43,960
You just said...

51
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,400
that you saw us holding hands.

52
00:03:46,759 --> 00:03:47,840
If I remember correctly,

53
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,400
my hand wasn't even open at that time.

54
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:53,039
She was the one gripping my hand tightly.

55
00:03:54,199 --> 00:03:55,400
In front of so many people,

56
00:03:55,520 --> 00:03:56,920
I couldn't just shake her hand off.

57
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,159
Besides,

58
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:00,919
this is a group photo.

59
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:04,400
Isn't it normal for people to stand close to each other?

60
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,521
Those who are in her Moments are all her social networks.

61
00:04:09,879 --> 00:04:12,599
She must have her reasons for posting this photo.

62
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,399
When are you going to make her face reality?

63
00:04:16,730 --> 00:04:18,570
What makes you think I didn't make any effort?

64
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:21,839
Last night,

65
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,120
when I sent her home.

66
00:04:23,121 --> 00:04:24,521
I wanted to take the opportunity...

67
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,399
to tell her about our relationship.

68
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,920
I hadn't even gotten...

69
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:31,730
to the main point yet.

70
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:33,439
She suddenly dashed into the kitchen,

71
00:04:33,759 --> 00:04:34,839
took a knife,

72
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,320
and hurt herself like this.

73
00:04:42,730 --> 00:04:44,290
Do you want to see her medical records?

74
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,079
Because of this,

75
00:04:50,519 --> 00:04:51,799
I didn't sleep a wink all night.

76
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:03,359
However, come to think of it,

77
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,920
you're right.

78
00:05:06,730 --> 00:05:08,439
All this trouble is because of me.

79
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:11,519
It's my fault.

80
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:14,560
I was hoping...

81
00:05:15,050 --> 00:05:16,170
to get some understanding...

82
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:18,399
and comfort from you,

83
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:20,730
but looking at it now,

84
00:05:25,839 --> 00:05:26,839
I was wrong.

85
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
It's unfair to you.

86
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,800
Go home.

87
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,920
I'm sorry, Zhou Zhou.

88
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,399
I was too willful.

89
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:09,360
Don't be angry.

90
00:06:20,519 --> 00:06:21,799
Do I have the right to be angry?

91
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,279
I don't.

92
00:06:28,639 --> 00:06:29,720
I'm just a little tired.

93
00:06:50,079 --> 00:06:51,120
Good news.

94
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:52,720
What is it?

95
00:06:53,519 --> 00:06:55,480
Haven't you always wanted to learn from Ms. Zeng?

96
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:56,879
Here's your chance.

97
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,759
What chance?

98
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:01,120
Ms. Zeng has secured...

99
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:03,016
the full series of ads for Biyuzan beauty products.

100
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:05,360
She aims to collaborate with us on the strategic aspects.

101
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,560
She's leading the formation of a new team...

102
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,640
and specifically inviting you to join.

103
00:07:11,879 --> 00:07:12,920
Me?

104
00:07:13,079 --> 00:07:14,160
Why?

105
00:07:14,319 --> 00:07:15,480
What do you mean why?

106
00:07:15,519 --> 00:07:16,879
She thinks you're doing well.

107
00:07:17,079 --> 00:07:18,120
By the way,

108
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,638
we have to go to Ms. Zeng's company now...

109
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:20,719
for a meeting with the client.

110
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,800
Hurry up and get ready.

111
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,720
Now?

112
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:24,879
Yes.

113
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,839
We'll showcase the history of the Biyuzan brand...

114
00:07:44,959 --> 00:07:46,199
and its evolving products...

115
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,199
since the 1970s,

116
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:51,360
ultimately focusing on the newly launched toner.

117
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,600
Last night,

118
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:54,319
when I sent her home.

119
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,600
I wanted to take the opportunity...

120
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,560
to tell her about our relationship.

121
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:00,760
I hadn't even gotten to the main point yet.

122
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,800
She dashed into the kitchen,

123
00:08:01,801 --> 00:08:02,879
took a knife,

124
00:08:03,279 --> 00:08:04,399
and hurt herself like this.

125
00:08:04,839 --> 00:08:06,360
It conveys the concept...

126
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,560
that everything in the past is merely a prologue.

127
00:08:15,519 --> 00:08:17,040
What do you think?

128
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,439
The product...

129
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,720
is closely related to its value.

130
00:08:24,879 --> 00:08:25,919
The direction is very clear.

131
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:27,000
Yes.

132
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,318
I want to hear everyone's opinions.

133
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:30,319
Yes.

134
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:31,720
What do you think?

135
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,519
Sun Han Han.

136
00:08:40,639 --> 00:08:41,679
What do you think?

137
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:44,399
Let me introduce you.

138
00:08:44,679 --> 00:08:45,719
Sun Han Han...

139
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,798
is a very talented advertising creative...

140
00:08:46,799 --> 00:08:47,799
in our company.

141
00:08:50,879 --> 00:08:52,799
I think this proposal...

142
00:08:53,519 --> 00:08:56,279
has a strong classical vibe in its historical presentation.

143
00:08:56,559 --> 00:08:57,639
It's very good.

144
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,799
However, I feel that...

145
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:02,399
it comes off as a bit aloof...

146
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:03,919
and pretentious.

147
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,360
I don't know why,

148
00:09:06,799 --> 00:09:08,759
but it gives off an older vibe.

149
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:15,399
This is just my immediate impression.

150
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:16,720
It's still not quite polished.

151
00:09:26,919 --> 00:09:27,919
Bosses.

152
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,159
What do you think?

153
00:09:29,639 --> 00:09:30,879
Does it give off an older vibe?

154
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:32,720
How about this?

155
00:09:32,919 --> 00:09:34,426
Let's hear the young people's opinions...

156
00:09:34,450 --> 00:09:36,239
from our team.

157
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:37,240
(Thank you for watching)

158
00:09:37,279 --> 00:09:38,330
What do you think?

159
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,039
What do you think?

160
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,600
It seems a bit old-fashioned.

161
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,879
Well, Ms. Zeng,

162
00:09:52,090 --> 00:09:53,159
what do you think?

163
00:09:58,919 --> 00:10:01,200
I think Sun Han Han's opinion can be used as a reference.

164
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:03,210
Her instincts are usually pretty spot-on.

165
00:10:04,559 --> 00:10:07,159
As an old brand facing new challenges,

166
00:10:08,519 --> 00:10:11,210
why don't we take a completely different approach?

167
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:14,890
We can drop the pretentiousness of being an established brand...

168
00:10:15,450 --> 00:10:18,720
and focus on highlighting warmth and companionship...

169
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,720
to connect with the emotions...

170
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:22,135
and feelings of the younger generation.

171
00:10:22,159 --> 00:10:23,159
For example,

172
00:10:23,279 --> 00:10:24,759
we could create...

173
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:26,640
a character of an unnoticed office worker.

174
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,450
That way, it's easier to interact with young people...

175
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:32,759
and get them to embrace the new brand and product.

176
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:36,639
That's why young people's opinions should be taken into account.

177
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,480
(Rucheng Group)

178
00:10:44,330 --> 00:10:45,359
Ms. Zeng.

179
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,399
Ms. Zeng.

180
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:48,600
There's a budget report that needs your signature.

181
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:49,720
Okay.

182
00:10:50,090 --> 00:10:51,240
I'm sorry about just now.

183
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,720
I didn't think it through and blurted it out.

184
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:56,079
I shouldn't have done it in front of the client.

185
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,800
You don't have to apologize to me.

186
00:10:58,919 --> 00:11:00,440
Work with me once and you'll know.

187
00:11:00,799 --> 00:11:03,000
I love disruptive ideas the most.

188
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:04,976
The most important thing in our line of work...

189
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,280
is to have your own perspective.

190
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,720
If you think it's right, stick to it.

191
00:11:09,039 --> 00:11:10,360
Don't worry about the client...

192
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:12,039
and the boss.

193
00:11:12,879 --> 00:11:13,959
But you can't just be the one who cuts ideas...

194
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,080
without providing solutions.

195
00:11:15,519 --> 00:11:18,200
You need to offer more ideas for the unnoticed worker proposal.

196
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,279
I will.

197
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:28,039
Ms. Zeng, what happened to your hand?

198
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,960
We have a house under renovation.

199
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,920
On a whim, I wanted to check out the construction site.

200
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,000
The temporary power at the site was out...

201
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,160
and it was completely dark.

202
00:11:38,279 --> 00:11:39,639
I accidentally tripped and fell.

203
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,120
Last night,

204
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:42,879
when I sent her home.

205
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:45,440
I wanted to take the opportunity...

206
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,159
to tell her about our relationship.

207
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,416
I hadn't even gotten to the main point yet.

208
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:50,518
She dashed into the kitchen,

209
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:51,639
took a knife,

210
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,559
and hurt herself like this.

211
00:11:55,559 --> 00:11:56,799
When Zeng Cheng was in college,

212
00:11:56,919 --> 00:11:58,056
she suffered from bipolar disorder.

213
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:59,480
She got better after treatment.

214
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:02,159
I'm worried that the divorce will provoke her.

215
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,960
That sounds painful.

216
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,839
You're seriously injured.

217
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:10,200
Why are you still working so hard?

218
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:11,879
I'm fine.

219
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:14,360
To me, this injury is nothing.

220
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,120
I'll get going then.

221
00:12:59,799 --> 00:13:01,440
What are you so focused on listening to?

222
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,559
Schumann.

223
00:13:02,639 --> 00:13:03,679
You know it.

224
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:06,080
Come, I'll show you something.

225
00:13:14,559 --> 00:13:15,600
Look.

226
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,680
It's the renovation plan for our new house.

227
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,440
This is the bedroom.

228
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:25,439
- It's nice. - Yes.

229
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:27,559
I want the whole space to feel cleaner...

230
00:13:27,879 --> 00:13:29,039
and have a warmer tone.

231
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,240
This is the kitchen.

232
00:13:31,679 --> 00:13:33,038
I'm in charge of the kitchen.

233
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:34,039
No problem.

234
00:13:34,879 --> 00:13:36,840
I'll choose the biggest fridge.

235
00:13:37,639 --> 00:13:39,278
Look at the stove and the sink.

236
00:13:39,279 --> 00:13:40,559
They're all my favourites.

237
00:13:40,759 --> 00:13:42,240
Let me show you the living room.

238
00:13:44,559 --> 00:13:45,918
This way, the whole space is bright.

239
00:13:45,919 --> 00:13:47,000
Right?

240
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:52,200
I've been thinking lately...

241
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,720
about the gym in our new house.

242
00:13:55,159 --> 00:13:56,240
Why don't we get rid of it?

243
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:57,399
Don't.

244
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,799
Do you want to expand your dressing room?

245
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,440
No.

246
00:14:04,799 --> 00:14:06,319
I want to reserve a room for our kids.

247
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,120
Are you kidding me?

248
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,919
Are you being spontaneous again?

249
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:19,720
I'm serious.

250
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,440
We're talking about a kid here.

251
00:14:24,519 --> 00:14:25,639
Have you thought it through?

252
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:29,320
I've always been curious.

253
00:14:30,519 --> 00:14:32,360
If there were someone in the world...

254
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:33,799
who looked like me...

255
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:35,120
and also looked like you,

256
00:14:36,559 --> 00:14:37,759
what would they be like?

257
00:14:38,320 --> 00:14:39,360
All right.

258
00:14:39,720 --> 00:14:42,080
Stop tempting me.

259
00:14:42,879 --> 00:14:44,399
You're the one who wants to be a dink.

260
00:14:44,679 --> 00:14:45,999
You're the one who wants a child.

261
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:48,039
In the end, you're the one who doesn't want it.

262
00:14:48,519 --> 00:14:50,359
I won't believe you anymore.

263
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,360
Stop mentioning it.

264
00:14:54,159 --> 00:14:55,960
I really won't change my mind this time.

265
00:14:57,639 --> 00:14:59,360
I can still have kids at my age,

266
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:02,480
but it's almost the last chance.

267
00:15:03,919 --> 00:15:06,519
Perhaps it's this urgency...

268
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,759
that makes me want a child.

269
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,160
Have you really thought about it?

270
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,120
Are you sure you're serious?

271
00:15:19,039 --> 00:15:20,080
Let me tell you.

272
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:22,159
Someone once told me...

273
00:15:22,679 --> 00:15:24,320
that women reach a certain point...

274
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:27,519
when they feel an ancient calling.

275
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,279
It's a call...

276
00:15:29,639 --> 00:15:31,120
that no one can resist.

277
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:32,799
At that time, I thought,

278
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:34,678
"How could that be?"

279
00:15:34,679 --> 00:15:35,919
"Isn't that just brainwashing?"

280
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,519
But now I realize...

281
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,840
it's actually an instinct...

